<p>How to get text advance (stringWidth) without a <code>Graphics</code> instance in Java?</p>  <p>In the <a href="https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/2d/text/measuringtext.html" rel="nofollow">doc examples</a>, <code>stringWidth()</code> is taken from <code>FontMetrics</code>, while <code>FontMetrics</code> is taken from <code>Graphics</code>.</p>  <p>Is it possible to obtain the same without a <code>Graphics</code>?</p>  <p>In the notes below it is said, that <code>Graphics</code> is required because it holds <code>FontRenderContext</code>. But I have <code>FontRenderContext</code>, just have no <code>Graphics</code>.</p>  <p>So, suppose I have <code>FontRenderContext</code> without a <code>Graphics</code>. How do I get <code>stringWidth()</code> then?</p>